    "notes": "Breton (Brezhoneg). ~200,000 speakers (est. 2020). Brittany, France. Brought from Britain by insular Brythonic speakers (~5thвҖ“6th c. CE). Four main dialects: LГ©onard (KLT basis), TrГ©gorrois, Cornouaillais, Vannetais (most divergent). вҹЁc'hвҹ© = /x/; вҹЁzhвҹ© = /z/ (KLT) or /h/ (Vannetais). French strongly influenced phonology (uvular /КҒ/, nasal vowels in loans). Refs: Hemon (1975), Press (1986).",
